msgid "The set of supported @env{TZ} strings is system-dependent.  GNU and many other systems support the tzdata database, e.g., @samp{\"America/New_York\"} specifies the time zone and daylight saving time history for locations near New York City.  GNU and most other systems support POSIX-style @env{TZ} strings, e.g., @samp{\"EST+5EDT,M4.1.0/2,M10.5.0/2\"} specifies the rules used in New York from 1987 through 2006.  All systems support the string @samp{\"UTC0\"} meaning Universal Time."
